The paper deals with the problem of sparse signal recovery, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and statistics (cs.SI). The use of random Gaussian measurement matrices is also a common technique in compressed sensing, which is a subfield of all these categories. Therefore, it is likely that this paper could be classified under any of these categories, with cs.IT and cs.LG being the most likely due to the focus on sparse signal recovery.
